{"article_id":"DBWcD592lLgz73WI","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"WASHINGTON -","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"Americans are not clamoring for single-payer health care ,","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"as Sen. Bernie Sanders suggests","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"they are ,","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"in proposing a plan","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"that would have the government foot most medical bills .","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"He 's right","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"that support for the idea has grown","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"and in some polls tops 50 percent .","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"But polls suggest","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"that the prevailing sentiment is ambivalence .","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"Saving money on health insurance holds lots of appeal .","depth":5},{"id":12,"text":"Seeing taxes rise","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"to cover those costs","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"may dull the appetite .","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"Sanders ' plan ,","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"released Wednesday ,","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"would have the government finance coverage","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"now paid for by a mix of employers , their workers , public plans and people in the individual insurance market .","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"He 's not given details of the likely cost or how , exactly , he 'd pay for it .","depth":5},{"id":20,"text":"A look at the independent Vermont senator 's claims about the popularity of a government-financed system and how they compare with surveys of public opinion :","depth":6},{"id":21,"text":"- '' You mean","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"because the people in this country want to move toward a Medicare-for-all system ,","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"that is divisive ?","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"I think","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"in a democracy , we should be doing what the American people want . ''","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"- AP interview Tuesday ,","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"when asked about divisions in the Democratic Party over his idea .","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"- '' Guaranteeing health care as a right is important to the American people not just from a moral and financial perspective ;","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"it also happens to be what the majority of the American people want . ''","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"- Opinion piece in The New York Times on Wednesday .","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"It takes a selective use of polling","depth":6},{"id":32,"text":"to make that case .","depth":6},{"id":33,"text":"Overall , public opinion research delivers decidedly mixed results .","depth":5},{"id":34,"text":"The Kaiser Family Foundation reports a `` modest increase '' in support for single-payer coverage in recent years , with `` substantial '' opposition .","depth":5},{"id":35,"text":"Perhaps most notably , public opinion is `` malleable , ''","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"with support dropping","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"when people are presented with arguments against it","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"that are certain to emerge in the debate .","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"Kaiser 's tracking poll in July found 53 percent in favor","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"of having all Americans get their health insurance from the government ;","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"43 percent were against that .","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"Opposition climbed to 60 percent","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"when people were asked to consider","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"that such a plan would call for higher taxes for many .","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"A slight majority also swung against a single-payer plan","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"when respondents were told","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"that former President Barack Obama 's health care law would be replaced as a result .","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"Public opinion research also helps to explain","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"why Sanders calls his plan `` Medicare for all . ''","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"Labels matter .","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"People tend to react more favorably to the notion","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"of expanding the popular Medicare program","depth":12},{"id":53,"text":"to cover everyone","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"than to the idea of `` single-payer ''","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"even if they amount to the same thing .","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"-People were about evenly divided in an AP-NORC Center survey in January , 39 percent against having everyone get their health insurance from one government plan and 38 percent in favor .","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"Support dropped substantially","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"when the prospect of a large increase in federal spending was introduced .","depth":12},{"id":59,"text":"-Respondents favored a Medicare-for-all plan 51-38 in a Quinnipiac poll in August","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"that did not raise the question of potential costs .","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"-In his Times article , Sanders cited an Economist/YouGov poll in April","depth":13},{"id":62,"text":"that found a clear preference","depth":15},{"id":63,"text":"for expanding Medicare","depth":16},{"id":64,"text":"to provide health insurance to all","depth":16},{"id":65,"text":"- 60-23 .","depth":14},{"id":66,"text":"The survey did not address the cost or tax implications","depth":13},{"id":67,"text":"of taking that course .","depth":13},{"id":68,"text":"That survey was conducted","depth":12},{"id":69,"text":"using an opt-in online panel","depth":14},{"id":70,"text":"recruited with internet advertising ,","depth":14},{"id":71,"text":"a methodology","depth":14},{"id":72,"text":"criticized by some","depth":15},{"id":73,"text":"because of concerns","depth":16},{"id":74,"text":"that it does not reach a random sample of Americans .","depth":16},{"id":75,"text":"-The Pew Research Center in June found","depth":13},{"id":76,"text":"60 percent","depth":15},{"id":77,"text":"who believe","depth":16},{"id":78,"text":"the federal government is responsible","depth":17},{"id":79,"text":"for ensuring health care coverage for all Americans ,","depth":17},{"id":80,"text":"with 39 percent disagreeing .","depth":14},{"id":81,"text":"That supports Sanders ' contention","depth":15},{"id":82,"text":"that people want health care as a right .","depth":15},{"id":83,"text":"But ensuring coverage is not the same as paying for it .","depth":14},{"id":84,"text":"Support for a single-payer system registered at only 33 percent in that poll .","depth":13},{"id":85,"text":"Many of those","depth":13},{"id":86,"text":"who felt","depth":14},{"id":87,"text":"the government has a responsibility","depth":15},{"id":88,"text":"for making sure","depth":16},{"id":89,"text":"people have coverage","depth":16},{"id":90,"text":"instead supported a mix of public and private programs .","depth":12}],"relations":[{"parent":181,"left":0,"right":180,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":180,"left":104,"right":179,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":104,"left":95,"right":103,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":95,"left":93,"right":94,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":93,"left":1,"right":92,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":92,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":94,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":103,"left":99,"right":102,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":99,"left":97,"right":98,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":97,"left":6,"right":96,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":96,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":98,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":102,"left":11,"right":101,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":101,"left":100,"right":14,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":100,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":179,"left":121,"rig